,Recommended,253650,9084695,"Posted: 13 February, 2014",all,GENGHIS KHAN DID NOTHING WRONG,"Interesting game but still feels somewhat static. (Don't expect Spore Cell Stage nor Flow)As someone with a great intrest for evolution and with a weak spot for every game that tries to simulate evolution I had to try this game. At first sight this game reminded me of Flow (awesome game), and not as much of the Spore Cell Stage as others where saying. If you're expecting a game like Spore, don't buy this game.Due to the beautiful and original visuals the game feels wonderous, mysterious and very alien. But nonetheless the first few stages of this game are very boring and confusing (imo). You're really waiting for stuff to happen, but instead you only get to eat blue, green and red balls untill you ate enough of them to finish the stage. After eating enough of these balls, you'll level up and you're creature will change it's form, but that doesn't really feel like evolution.After a few stages of boringness other creatures start to appear you can eat, even bosses you can eat and defeat. This was quite a (positive) surprise to me. At this point I realized there was atually some challenge to this game. See, throughout the game you've got a 'nemesis' who will try to eat as much as it can, just like you, after you or you're nemesis has prodominemntly ate most of the food in that particular stage, one of you will win. I think that is pretty cool and original.What's also a cool aspect of this game is that your creature will gain all kinds of stats that will improve your creature performances, I haven't played around with that much so I don't wan't to say to much about it. But I think that is part of the game that is meant to be the evolution part.I feel like this game needs more polishing, it just doens't feel complete. I would like to see more evolution aspects and more challenge, that isn't repetitive."
