,Not Recommended,253650,8956106,"Posted: 2 February, 2014",all,<M.o.K>Samurai Jack-ing Off,"A game that was heavily inspired by the game flOw.The core concept sounds fun and should be enjoyable, the gameplay is marred by horrid controls and really imprecise movement. You feel like you're trying to guide a tank, not a snake-like organism.Similar to flOw, there are multiple layers you can transit through in each section. Each layer contains various other enemies and DNA strands you can consume. The different types of DNA alter your creature's genome, enabling different characteristics. This concept is central to the game, and quite innovative.The visual design is superb, with great design cues for the various creatures. The environment feels bare, but that can serve to help focus your attention.Music is relaxing and sounds are unobtrusive.With better implemented controls and movement, this might have been a fun game. As it stands, I'd avoid it."
