76561198145854836,Recommended,253650,16131948,"Posted: 2 June, 2015",all,Unclenched,"Well... this is a surprise.I've had this game for about 20 minutes at the time of writing this review, but I gotta say I'm already amazed. For future reference, I bought this game during a steam sale but I might have just bought it full price if I discovered it before now.ART 10/10So, the art of the game is very veryveeeerrrrygood, so much so I would say its the highlight of this game, despite the other features. It is absolutely stunning. I have a decent PC so I immediately turned the graphics up to full, and they do not disappoint. These are some of the best visuals I've seen, with everything from the color-faded background to the transparent 3-D 'walls'. I love these graphics.MUSIC 8/10The music has a kind of tranquil feeling to it, and helps to relax into the game. It flows very well with the gameplay, and the sound effects aren't dominating over it, nor vice versa. There is a very good balance here in my opinion.GAMEPLAY 6/10This is pretty good as well, although its not a revolutionary game in this aspect. I have had fun so far playing this game, and I think I will continue to do so, but the art and the music are the main hooks for me. It has a very similar feeling to the early stage of Spore, but it is the entire game. If you liked that, you would probably like this game.STORY 2/10You are evolving a thing. That's it. That's the whole story. Not that this game really needs a story.CONCLUSION 7.5/10This game is very fun and relaxing to play, and is great if you have a spare 5 minutes to kill.  This game doesn't quite make it to an 8 as I don't think it has the ability to entertain for a long period of time. Also, some of the mechanics in the game could use some refining but that's just me. I would recommend this game, though getting it in a sale is probably best."
