76561197977670949,Recommended,253650,16370913,"Posted: 13 June, 2015",all,biostudent,"Picked up this nice little game on sale. Very cheap. Under a buck.You control a ""creature"" and move it around to eat things. You have the option to eat red, blue, or green things. Each one will help shape your creature. Red to make a carnivore, blue for an omnivore, green for an omnivore. Each type has different eating speed, movement speed, and maneuverability. There are 14 stages. You have two options for play. Solo or vs computer AI. In solo mode you need to have your creature eat all of one color of items in a level to clear it. In ""competitive""/vs computer mode your creature must consume more of/all of one color object before the computer controlled creature does.Controls are simple, either point and click with mouse scroll wheel to move up and down in depth, or keyboard. Simple controls, fun to play. The background music is nice ambient music. The visuals are great, lots of transparency and light.It's short, but still very fun for the short time it takes to finish it."
