76561198073236550,Recommended,253650,16209126,"Posted: 5 June, 2015",all,Genesius,"I'm going to start right off the bat saying that I agree with other players of this game, it isn't for everyone. I snagged this game for 74 cents. The game itself is simple, you are an organism that goes around in the level eating other microorganisms to level up all while competing against an AI. The more you eat, the more you grow.Hands down, the graphics are gorgeous. The game is beautiful, especially when you get your organism to a high level. Even running it at ""Good"" settings in the launcher, I was shocked. Everything is so bright (except for the first few stages of the game, which have a darker yellow-brownish kind of background).The gameplay is debateable. Some find it boring, others find it good. People argue it's boring because you only get so many options for leveling and there isn't much diversity in power. This game has a casual tag for a reason. I think it's good enough given the games length and cost. Don't go into this game thinking it's going to be as epic as Skyrim or something. It's gameplay is simple and calm. (Though when you turn your organism into a bottomless eating machine, it's fun to sprint around killing other organisms and steal them from your opponent!)The music: awesome, though it all depends on your taste of music.In a nutshell, the game is as good as it's going to get. The sights and sounds are amazing, and the amount of action you are going to get in this game all varies on your playstyle.Overall: 8/10, would eat again."
