,Recommended,253650,31952036,Posted: 25 May,all,E-200 Paragon,"For a knockoff, this game certainly deserves recognition.SummarySparkle 2: Evo is a top-down game based on the flash game known asflOw.In flOw, you play as a serpentine creature whose sole purpose is to eat other creatures.As you descend, the enemies gain more hitpoints and become harder to kill.At the bottom is a powerful creature that is fast and dangerous that you have to defeat.Once you beat the final boss, the game resets and then control a jellyfish-like creature.You then have to repeat the process with your previous creature now serving as the final boss.Once you beat the final boss again, the game resets with the original serpentine creature.The game got so popular that a port was developed and released for all PlayStation platforms.Now that you know what flOw is, let's get to the summary of Sparkle 2 Evo.This game is literally a stylized PC version of flOw.You play as the aforementioned serpentine creature known as a Sparkle.Along with the traditional mechanics found in flOw, you also get to choose between three different variants based on what you consume throughout each zone.Each variant has a special ability that changes the gameplay and difficulty.You'll know which one the Sparkle will become based on the colored trail it leaves as it swims.The transformation happens automatically upon filling up your Experience Bar.If you eat anything that glows red, you will become a Carnivore.The Carnivore is fast and maneuverable, but can be hard to control sometimes.Its special ability is Lunge, which shoots the Sparkle forward extremely fast.If you eat anything that glows green, you will become a Herbivore.The Herbivore is bulky and tough but is slow and cannot turn that well.Its special ability is Inhale, which automatically collects any food within range of its mouth.If you eat anything that glows blue, you will become an Omnivore.The Omnivore is a jack-of-all-trades since it has the strengths and weaknesses of both sides.Its special ability is Screech, which makes all animals run away from you for a short time.ProblemsYou would think that since it's based on such a popular game with such a simple design and mechanics, there wouldn't be that many problems with this game right? (ha ha ha, WRONG!)For one thing, the Sparkle variants all move and turn at the same speed.That means it doesn't matter which type you are since only the special abilities are different.In addition, it only takes one hit from ANY predator to force you back up one level.The second problem is that the camera is in a fixed position that spins around the Sparkle.Imagine trying to walk while constantly looking at your feet and bobbing your head in a circle.In other words, your field of view is hindered by the camera's motion since you won't be able to see what's in front of you until the camera spins around to reveal what's in front of you.There are other problems as well, but I have to keep my reviews within a tolerable length.ConclusionAside from the problems, this is a very amazing game.The levels are surreal, the music is lovely, and the graphics look fantastic.However, I'll be honest, the ending was very disappointing considering flOw had a final boss.Regardless, it still achieved the same goal as flOw did, which is immersive relaxation."
,Not Recommended,253650,14841968,"Posted: 11 March, 2015",all,みoƦƦoƦ ₣o父,Hey everyone and this is my review about the game!This is a casual game.Interface/Menu/SettingsThere are some different resolution sizes available.You can play fullscreen or windowed mode.There is a sound volume slidebar available.There is a music volume slidebar available.There are some profile slots available.There is a manual available.About the game.You are playing with a little Evo thing tnat has to collect sparkles. You can go deeper or swim up by scrolling the mouse wheel to find the sparkles. You will start with a small evo spark and has to eat the smaller ones in order to evolve bigger. As you have turned bigger you are also able to eat the bigger sparkles and your evo will change too.  In Competitive mode you will fight against an Ai that is doing the same thing as you are and you are able to win the game if you have eaten more sparkles then he does.Controls that you need to get used too.Has ingame tutorial.Very Repetitive.There is a pause button.Okay Graphics.$5 bucks is a bit too much what the game has to offer.Other things.None.-------------------I Give this game a 1/10
