,Not Recommended,253650,29886357,Posted: 12 February,all,Omnifarious,"This is kind of a meandering game in which the objectives are not terribly clear. And, unlike Flow, it's clear that the game was written with actual objectives in mind.So, that makes this game a poorly executed knockoff of Flow, which was/is an excellent game. I do not generally mind copycat games, especially if they at least bring something new to the table and are executed at least as well as the original. But, while this game does bring something new to the table (you are what you eat) its poor execution leaves it a pale imitator rather than an evolutionary innovator."
76561198036472461,Not Recommended,253650,29748703,Posted: 6 February,all,Threnodia,"It feels like this ""game""'s sole purpose is the mingling of beautiful graphics and sound. And this is ok, if relaxing colors are what you want. It was for me, because after reading a few reviews, I didn't expect more (and got it on sale).But: I cannot play the game for more than ten minutes straight, because the constant circling and the general ""fluffiness"" of the movements just make me feel dizzy. After 15 minutes, this starts to turn into sickness.So as great as the game looks, people prone to seasickness might get problems."
76561198008048750,Recommended,253650,8535645,"Posted: 3 January, 2014",all,Ryo,"It is exactly what the developers said themselves ""a game to waste time and have some fun"". It has surprisingly good 2D graphics and the sounds fits well, at least you like smooth electronic music. The gameplay is simple and for such a few money (< 5 €) i am not complaining about the noticed bugs."
,Recommended,253650,35454722,Posted: 3 October,all,QcKLU,"It was on sale for €0.49 when I bought it... Was kinda fun to play... Don't think it would be worth buying for the full price...It's basically a simplified version of the spore cell stage but with better graphics, nicer music and more relaxing gameplay"
,Recommended,253650,35510890,Posted: 5 October,all,Verdantil,"Tags: Clicker - FastTLDR: Presents like a life simulation but really is just pellet gobbler in semi open environment.  Concept is short lived and the game has design issues but it is pleasant. Lack of minimap and worse radar than games in this franchise but everything else feels better.Simple game in which you hold mouse1 to swim around and eat pellets, and use mousewhell to change Z level and eat more pellets. Play casual mode and go on an easter egg for pellets of certain colors. Competitive mode has other fishes that eat pellets as well making it a race against the clock. The game is eye catching and somewhat immersive but gets disorienting and repetitive with underdevelopped concepts. Lacks the feeling of a living breathing ecosystem that you survive in, and just feels like a reskinned pellet eating arcade game with design issues. You would probably be better off playing Spore or Insaniquarium. But this is probably the best entry in this series so if you are going to keep one, it might as well be this one."
